                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/12609.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Brazilian Minister</gloss> to Mexico to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Brazilian Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 24, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>96. Department’s 170, July 23. As the result of a long conversation I had with
                    the President yesterday he told me this afternoon that he had decided to appoint
                    two delegates to go to Saltillo by way of San Luis Potosi as suggested in
                    Department’s July 20, 10 p.m. By tomorrow or perhaps tonight I will know and
                    transmit to you their names and date of departure from here. President Carbajal
                    also expressed his desire that Constitutionalist delegates be at Saltillo on the
                    arrival of his, so that negotiations may be started at once. He also told me
                    that inasmuch as he has de facto stopped all hostilities against
                    Constitutionalists it would please him very much if an arrangement could be made
                    to have them do likewise from now on, with the proviso that when delegates meet
                    the matter may be duly ratified.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cardoso de Oliveira</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
